Defendant Mary Jo C McMullen in court, in custody, with attorney Nicholas Martinez.   Bryan Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   The Read-In List filed by the State on 3/15/16 is not accepted by the Court and withdrawn by the State.  The parties address indescrepencies in the PSI and make corrections on the record.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

4 YEARS 6 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 315 days)(commencing forthwith)
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  Any Panera Bread, Pick N Save N. Calhoun Road, Alice C.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Any other condition deemed appropriate by agent.

RESTITUTION:  $811.40 total ($40.00 payable to Panera Bread, $421.40 payable to Citi Bank, and $350.00 payable to Roundy's) (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines, 20% of prison wages to be applied to Restitution/Costs);

